It sounds like your best bet is probably to set the opacity of the target element to 1, run ramjet, set opacity back to 0, _then_ fade in:

``` js
target.style.opacity = 1;
ramjet.transform(source, target, {...});
target.style.opacity = 0;

fadeIn(target);
```
